function greetUser(name, greeting = "Hello") {
    return greeting + " " + name;
}


Example
console.log(greetUser("Rohan"));         
// Output: Hello Rohan

console.log(greetUser("Ritik", "Good Morning")); 
// Output: Good Morning Rohan


Approach:

(Logic)

Create a function named greetUser.

The function should take two parameters:

name

greeting (set this as a default parameter, e.g., "Hello").

If the user does not provide a greeting, the function will use the default greeting.

Combine the greeting and name to create a message.

Return the greeting message.
